         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Robert (BCH 1928, 44, and Hellenica 13, 174) pointed out that this man is agent of the senator, not his son, as suggested by Boeckh, and accepted by Reinach, and Vagts, <title>among</title> others although the point had already been made by E. Groag, Jahreshefte 10 (1907) 297, n. 52</p>
